Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add a minimal main menu: application menu (Quit), Shell (New Window Cmd-N, Close
Window Cmd-W), and Edit (Copy Cmd-C, Paste Cmd-V, Select All Cmd-A). New Window
targets the app delegate (openTerminalWindow, now reusable and multi-window);
Copy/Paste/Select All target the first responder, implemented on TerminalView via
new bridge calls: bridge_copy_selection (Terminal::extractSelectionText ->
NSPasteboard), bridge_paste (NSPasteboard -> Terminal::sendPaste), bridge_select_all
(Terminal::selectAll). Cmd-C/V do not clash with the terminal's Ctrl-C/V, which are
Control (routed through keyDown to the engine).

Tabs and split panes are supported by the engine model (vtmux, already linked) but
not yet wired in the frontend; the menu/window structure leaves room to add them.

